You had it
poppin' tonight.
I totally disagree.
Because I love your look.
You're a star.
Believe in your dreams.

- Thank you.
- Jason,

have you ever put out a cigar

and his screams

Until tonight.

Congratulations,
you're a disgrace.
Ah! I rolled my ankle. God!

that show last night.

Not me. I've got

than watch Jenna
humiliate children.

made it to the next round?

- How? She is so pitchy.
- What can I tell you?

The audience just loves
Shayla's personal story.

Did you know that both her
mothers are serial killers?
That's America.

So, did you miss me

Of course. A little less than

but I did get
a nice Christmas card

from Avery
and Kim Jong-Un.

At least I had some
quality time with Liddy.

She's like a little

Donaghy?

If you want, I can recommend

You know, 'cause
I really like my guy.

He's sort of
a doogie howser type.
But younger.

Aren't you going
to ask me how my...

No. I know exactly
how your holidays were.

You took the train
to your parents' house.

On Christmas Eve, you forgot
that eggnog has alcohol in it,

and got into a shoving match
with your aunt

about who puts the star
on top of the tree.
It was my year!

What, lupus lets you
just cut the line?

You received two sweaters
that you didn't really like

and got your dad a book on world
war ii that he already owned.

Wow, you really think you know
everything about me, don't you?

Yes, after six years
I really do.
Well, I will have you know

that there are
aspects of my life

about which
you know nothing.
Take off that jacket.

If you're not wearing
one of those Christmas sweaters

out of guilt,
I'll give you $1,000.

Wrong, Jack.
'Cause they weren't sweaters.
They were Dickies!
Happy 2012!

Die, you blonde bitch!

She's adorable.

Thanks.

Oh. Ha. That's odd,

And I'm about

That sounds like

Okay, how about this?

Pay attention to me, L.L,

Why are you acting so weird?

I don't know what

You're not doing your job.
You're laughing at rectum jokes,

Did we switch brains?

Why am I not

Baah!

We need to talk about Kidz.

Did you see

What if you went the other way,

Well, no.

I mean, being the nice one

Ah, yes, well, we've done

No, Jack.
They love to hate me.

I mean,
look at Betty White.

Just ease off on the kids.
Look, according to Tracy,

That's obviously
what's happened.

So whoever you are,

That's for you.

Damn, I've got to get
more of these.
I don't know what this is,

but I like it.
Ha, finally.

That was on your list?

in a really good
place right now.

Well, enjoy it

you're going to women's hell.

Uh, also, FYI,

aroused dog heaven.
Kenneth.

Why are you still here?
This is your last day on Earth.

There's so much
you haven't done.

Oh, sir,
I've done plenty.

Oh, really?
Have you ever been in love?

Only while
playing tennis.

I'm kidding.
I've never played tennis.

Have you ever been
in an airplane?

Never?

We were all put on this crazy

Easy, d'Fwan.

Mommy.
